posts.message: Can someone guide me on where to start learning Python?
I recommend starting with the official Python documentation.
What IDE do you prefer for Java?
I've been using IntelliJ IDEA for years and love it.
Practice consistently and work on projects.
Contributing to open source is a great way to learn.
Learn to use a debugger and practice logging.
Understanding common errors helps a lot.
Microservices are a way to build applications using small, independent services.
They allow for greater flexibility and scalability.
Check out online courses on Coursera and edX.
Books like 'Hands-On Machine Learning' are great too.
Communication is key, use tools like Slack.
Regular virtual meetings help maintain alignment.
AI can help in diagnosing diseases early.
It's vital to address privacy concerns.
Blockchain can be used in supply chain management.
It's also useful for securing digital identities.
Quantum computing could revolutionize cryptography.
It's still in early stages but shows great promise.
